00:16.060 --> 00:18.060
Crazy.

00:18.060 --> 00:20.060
Did you notice?

00:20.060 --> 00:49.620
Here we have our first exercise in moving the

00:49.620 --> 01:00.340
shoulder over and you see you ideally want to be on the loose rein at the walk really initiating

01:00.340 --> 01:07.420
the shoulder movement from the leg. If there's any takeaway of today it's that the initiation

01:07.420 --> 01:13.420
has to come from the leg and not the rein. The rein just leads the horse to the leg. So as you

01:13.420 --> 01:20.540
see here sometimes you need to pick up the same rein that the leg is on so in this case the left

01:20.540 --> 01:27.300
rein in the left leg and the other way would be the right rein in the right leg to help the horse

01:27.300 --> 01:35.180
understand which side you want him to pay attention to. If you've completed that and the

01:35.180 --> 01:41.260
groundwork you're ready to do this in trot. Now this horse is coming off the rail quite far and

01:41.260 --> 01:47.220
he's able and flexible enough to bend through his body and through the rib cage and the neck

01:47.220 --> 01:53.500
quite well. If your horse isn't at that stage yet then just travel one to two feet off the rail.

01:53.500 --> 01:59.700
So here you can really see the initiation coming from the right leg moving the shoulder over. This

01:59.700 --> 02:05.020
isn't a leg yield you don't want them to be rigid and straight yet we just want to move the shoulder

02:05.020 --> 02:14.100
over from the leg. So move your leg forward as if you're traveling the front of your shin over the

02:14.100 --> 02:21.980
front of the shoulder blade and move the horse's shoulder over. You see in the canter the more

02:21.980 --> 02:27.660
advanced version of this keeping the same lead and moving the shoulder over and being able to

02:27.660 --> 02:34.260
move the shoulder over the other way. So the most important part is to think the initiation from the

02:34.260 --> 02:41.180
leg. Number two that the shoulder is leading the way and is on the appropriate side of the haunches.

02:41.180 --> 02:47.620
So in this case the left side and then the right side of the haunches. Away you go I'm super

02:47.620 --> 02:48.940
interested to see your videos.

